choices.text:
probably the increasing political awareness of the masses. People are now paying more attention to politics, which leads to debate and contestation amongst political parties...and about time too. The past few decades have seen one of the greatest HeelTurns of former political leaders in the this history of this country, to political parties where their basic ideology is in direct conflict with what they stood for when they were serving the public. Instead of re-inventing themselves to fit what seem to be a set of increasingly confused principles that they previously worked on to fit a new party. As a result, hordes of angry Liberals are now flocking overseas. In the minds of Labor, Liberal or National Party voters, the only reason to vote one of these people in would be to vote against the other party. There’s an increasing degree of madness about our politics lately, but there’s a glimmer of hope left out there. The flames of our new found political awareness are the beginnings of a well deserved REPRIEVE for Australia.

New media is also an interesting development. Persuasively sizzling youth which demonstrates that they are not only influential but smart enough to make a difference. New media enables them to do neither. New media has also been exposed for it's influence when the Democrats controlled the global internet. Apparently nobody noticed, or at least ignored it. But now that the Republicans are attempting to control new media, suddenly it is 'In our face'. It makes one call the partisan universe into question
